{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":3,"author":{"id":"e6c152d440109efdc7afc4e9ac4ac193043f8f68"},"timestamp":1482620923,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI2OTEwMzYyNQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/105#issuecomment-269103625"},"message":"You can consider frameservers to be specialized clients that we trust to a higher degree for a certain set of tasks (role/archetype). So there is possibly one frameserver for decode (parsers), one for encode (recording, streaming), one for terminal and so on - and they are written explicitly to fulfil that role.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"f1622a8c5af7c08684053b629b0c16c95b1c1b19"},"timestamp":1482656020,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI2OTExNDg2MA==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/105#issuecomment-269114860"},"message":"Thank you for response. I have more questions, if you do not mind.\nIf I want to write a program exclusive to arcan what should I do?  The program will be under visual management of druden. What API should I use?\nIs there a sample of \"Hello, world\"?","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"e6c152d440109efdc7afc4e9ac4ac193043f8f68"},"timestamp":1482656783,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI2OTExNTE0Mw==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/105#issuecomment-269115143"},"message":"Three options.\n\n1. Write a lua appl and use arcan_lwa /path/to/folder to start it. There's https://github.com/letoram/arcan/wiki/Exercises as a text guide for this, with the solutions in https://github.com/letoram/arcan/tree/master/tests/exercises here. The plus side to this is that you happen to get acquainted with the same API and code style that durden was written with - so you learn how to patch, fix and extend that in the process.\n\n2. (C) For a CLI application, there's the (near-future stable) TUI API, skeleton here: https://github.com/letoram/arcan/blob/master/tests/frameservers/tui_test/tui_test.c\n\n3. (C) There's also the unstable API (as in, be prepared to recompile when the arcan build changes), it's only documented in header files with my testing applications appearing here: https://github.com/letoram/arcan/tree/master/tests/frameservers","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"e6c152d440109efdc7afc4e9ac4ac193043f8f68"},"timestamp":1482796110,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI2OTI0OTc1NQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/105#issuecomment-269249755"},"message":"If you have more questions, grab me on IRC - it's typically way easier. Anyhow, closing the issue.","files":null},{"type":4,"author":{"id":"e6c152d440109efdc7afc4e9ac4ac193043f8f68"},"timestamp":1482796110,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDExOkNsb3NlZEV2ZW50OTA1MzA2MzM2"},"status":2}]}